  "title": "Operation Support Engineer (Pharma/Biotech)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Support document lifecycle (creation, review, approval, release, issue of effective version, reconciliation and archival) </li><li>Support GMP training activities </li><li>Support shopfloor activities (6S, cleanroom gowning, personnel flow paths, signages, movement of equipment and materials) </li><li>Support daily operations by working with manufacturing, quality, facility, safety and site admin teams and upkeep meeting dashboards</li><li>Support site visit and audit activities</li></ul><p><strong>About You:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Science or Engineering with 1 to 2 years of GMP / QA experience</li><li>Able to work well in fast paced environment with cross-functional teams</li><li>Competency in data visualization or project management tools is a plus</li></ul><p><strong>Duration</strong>: 12 months<br /><strong>Shift: Normal Shift</strong></p>",
